Q6,7 Effect modification

  • Add interaction term
  • Effect and 95%CI for each subgroup
    • Example
      • Effect for nonsmoker: exp(model$coef["vac"])
      • Effect for smoker: exp(model$coef["vac"] + model$coef["vac:smoking])
      • 95% for nonsmoker: exp(confint.default(model)["vac",])
      • 95% for smoker:
        • Find SE for smoker (pooled) = sqrt(a.var + b.var + 2*ab.cov) where a=vac, b=vac:smoking **see figure
          • by vcov(model)(variance-covariance of fitted model)
          • sqrt(vcov(model)[2,2], vcov(model)[5,5], 2*vcov(model)[2,5])
        • Hence 95% CI = effect ± 1.96*se exp(lr.fvs.s$coef["vac"]+lr.fvs.s$coef["vac:smoking"] + c(-1,1)*qnorm(0.975)*se.vac.smoker)

Q8 Collinearity checking and solution

  • Use vif
  • Solve by centering
    • flu$ct.age <- scale(flu$age, scale=F)
    • lr.fvs.act <- glm(flu~vac+shealth+vac*ct.age, data=flu, family=binomial)
    • vif(lr.fvs.act) #collinearity problem solved!

Q9 Mediation analysis

  • Baron and Kenny criteria
    • Also include confounder, effect modification etc
  • Don’t use sobel test coz binomial outcome!

Q10 Model selection

  • step.model <- stepAIC(lr.fv, scope = list(upper = ~vac+shealth+bmi+vac*age+vac*smoking, lower = ~vac)) #specify the scope from upper=full model include all variables to lower=only exposure
    • FYI: lr.fv is glm(flu~vac, data=flu, family=binomial)
